                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. consists of one quire. The boards are
                           missing. The original sewing is torn off. The quires were roughly
                           resewn. The bifolium 4-5 is sewn together from two single leafs; it was probably inserted later.
 f. 5 is damaged at the right upper edge and fol. 8 all
                           around.
 <locus target="#1rv">1rv</locus> is affected by humidity, so
                           part of the text is not fully legible.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" writtenLines="21">
                           <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <height/>
                              <width/>
                              <dim type="intercolumn"/>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="margin">
                              <dim type="top"/>
                              <dim type="bottom"/>
                              <dim type="right"/>
                              <dim type="left"/>
                              <dim type="intercolumn"/>
                           </dimensions>
                           <note/>
                           <ab type="ruling">21 on <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>, 5 on <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>.</ab>
                           <ab type="ruling">The ruling is not complete: most of the folios don’t
                              contain the horizontal rules; the exception is <locus from="7v" to="8rv">7v-8rv</locus> (7v, 8v are with miniature and 8r is
                              blank).</ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Pricking is visible.</ab>
                        </layout>
                        
