                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, regular hand of the <date notBefore="1400" notAfter="1500" cert="unknown">15th century (?)</date>.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red (brilliant vermillion).</seg>
                        
                        <seg type="rubrication">A few lines, alternating with black lines, on the
                           incipit page of Text I; names of the months and numerals for the hours in
                           Text II; numerals; elements of the punctuation signs.</seg>
                     
                     <seg type="script">Archaic
                        features:
                        <note>(1) angular forms of some letters as መ
                        ዐ</note>
                        <note>(2) the tops of መ ወ ሠ በ are slightly
                        slanted to the
                        left</note>
                        <note>(3) መ has the loops of triangular shape,
                        not completely separated (e.g. <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>
                        l.2)</note>
                        <note>(4) ሎ has the 7th order marker attached
                        directly at the body of the letter, without linking line (e.g. <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>,
                        l.6)</note>
                        <note>(5) the numerals are without dashes
                        above and
                        below</note>
                        <note>(6) ፬ is triangular and downwards
                        oriented (e.g., <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>)</note>
                        <note>(7) ፮ is with the loop open, looking
                        like a “compressed” ፯ (e.g., <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>)</note>
                        <note>(8) ፪ has the loops, closed, not
                        separated (e.g., <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>).</note></seg>
                        

                        <seg type="script">Spelling features: (1) in the tables of Text I, “Sane” is written as “Sanǝy” (ሰንይ) (<locus target="#3r">3r</locus>) and “Naḥāse” as “Naḥāsi” (ነሓሲ) (<locus target="#3v">3v</locus>);
                        <note>(2) in the miniatures, ሥዕለ is written as ስዕለ.</note>
                           <note>(3)In the tables of Text II, most of the numerals have the Amharic siffix -ኛ (<locus from="2v" to="3v">2v-3v</locus>, <locus target="#6r">6r</locus>).</note>
                        <note>In the miniatures, the legends are written in the same hand as the main text.</note></seg>

                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#4v"/>

                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1002Annunciation">Annunciation</ref>.</desc>Legend (upper part): <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኀበ፡ ዜነዋ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ለማርያም፡</foreign> “Where
                        Gabriel announced to Mary”.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#5r"/>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">The Virgin and Child</ref>. The archangels are at the sides. </desc>Legends

                        (upper part): <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስዕለ፡ ገብርኤል</foreign> “Image of Gabriel”; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስዕለ፡ ማርያም፡</foreign> “Image of Mary”;
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስዕለ፡ ሚካ[ኤ]ል</foreign>፡ “Image of Michael”. The script of the legends is in negative
                        (on a black background).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus from="6v" to="7r">Fols. 6v-7r: </locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1047Apostles">St. Apostles</ref>.</desc><desc>Legends on fol. 6v (from the upper part, left):
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጴጥሮስ[፡]</foreign> “Peter”; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስዕለ፡ በርተሎሜዎስ፡</foreign> “Image of Bartholomew”; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማቴዎስ[፡]</foreign> “Matthew”;
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዮሐንስ፡</foreign> “John”; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ያዕቆብ፡</foreign> “James”; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማቲያስ[፡] </foreign>“Matthias”.</desc><desc>
 Legends on fol. 7r
                           (from the upper part, left): <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሉቃስ[፡]</foreign> “Luke”; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ፊልጶስ፡</foreign> “Philip”; <foreign xml:lang="gez">እንድርያስ[፡]</foreign>
                           “Andrew”;<foreign xml:lang="gez"> ያዕቆብ፡</foreign> “James”; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቶማስ[፡]</foreign> “Thomas”; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ታዴዎስ፡</foreign> “Thaddeus”.</desc></decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4">
                        <locus target="#7v">Fol. 7v: </locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1014Evangelists">Evangelist</ref>. Surrounded by the Four Living Creatures. </desc><note>The frame of the miniature seems unfinished</note>.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5">
                        <locus target="#8v">Fol. 8v: </locus>
                        <desc><term key="cross" ana="#cross">Cross</term>.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote xml:id="d6"><locus from="1v" to="2r"/><locus from="2v" to="3v"/><desc>The tables for Texts I and II are finely decorated. The tables on
                        <locus from="1v" to="3r">1v-3r</locus> are decorated with zoomorphicmotifs, some of which are associated with legends: <locus target="#1v">1v</locus> (upper margin): ዶ[n.l.]ራ[n.l.] “?”; <locus target="#2v">2v</locus> (upper margin): <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጣዎስ፡</foreign> “peacock”, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጣዎስ፡</foreign>
                        “peacock”; <locus target="#2v">2v</locus> (below the text): <foreign xml:lang="gez">ባቡላ፡</foreign> “?”, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ባቡላ፡</foreign> “?”.</desc></decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
